# Explanation

- In `main.py`, no changes were needed for routing or backend logic as it already complies with the requirements.

- In `dashboard.html`, added the inclusion of the consolidated JavaScript file `static/js/scripts.js` in the `<head>` section.

- Changed the "back-to-dashboard" button to have the id `back-to-dashboard` and removed inline `onclick` to rely on the JS event listener.

- Created a new file `static/js/scripts.js` with the consolidated JavaScript code that attaches click event listeners to all buttons with id `back-to-dashboard` to navigate to the root URL `/`.

- This ensures consistent behavior for all "back-to-dashboard" buttons across all pages.

- The JavaScript code is clean, consolidated, and included in all pages that need it.

This satisfies the comments and ensures compliance with regulation #2 and #4.
